# Tech Blog — Public Security

`xingai-tech-blog` is a **public** repository. Treat every post as attacker-readable.

## Before writing or editing posts

Read `docs/PUBLIC-SECURITY.md` and apply its checklist.

## Hard bans in `posts/`

- Real operator emails (`@xingai.app` used for admin/auth/OTP).
- Secret values, API keys, JWTs, cookie names with bypass semantics.
- Active auth bypass mechanics: custom headers, `localStorage` keys, env allowlists with real values, UI “skip login” flows.
- Statements that production auth is missing, broken, or incomplete.
- Links to product-repo troubleshooting sections that document bypasses.

## Use instead

- `admin@your-domain`, `<FLY_SECRET>`, `<allowlist env var>`.
- “Interim testing paths live in private runbooks” — no how-to.
- “We are completing OAuth rollout” — not “OAuth is not configured.”
- Architecture ADR links without bypass instructions.

## Pre-push grep (review diff)

Search for: `@xingai.app`, `bypass`, `X-Invest`, `V2_ADMIN`, `localStorage`, `sk-`, `secret=`, `not configured`, `lacks full`.

Redact or move sensitive lines to the product repo’s private ops docs.
